For the last 2 weeks, I've been working on an MCP server for my Novation Circuit Tracks (in case you don't know what it is, is just a little device to make electronic music). The idea is simple: I want an AI Agent to be able to make music using my gear, so I gave it tools to do it so I can just say something like "Build me a melodic ambient song with a dark atmosphere" and see the AI just do it.&lt;p&gt;The whole project is Open Source (&lt;a href="https://github.com/namirsab/circuit-tracks-tools" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://github.com/namirsab/circuit-tracks-tools&lt;/a&gt;) and I've written about it in my blog in case you want to go into more details. It is a fun project
that includes reverse engineering of proprietary file formats.&lt;p&gt;Would love to hear feedback, both from Circuit Track owners and just in general, what do you think about this idea? Have you tried something similar?&lt;/p&gt;
